nodes.text: 1933 was a B1-series battle droid manufactured by Baktoid Combat Automata who served in the Trade Federation Droid Army. In 32 BBY, the battle droid was part of the forces deployed by the Trade Federation to the Naboo capital city of Theed during the invasion of the planet. 1933 was part of a group of droids led by the OOM command battle droid 2163 that were tasked with guarding the Naboo Royal Starship in the Theed Hangar.

The Federation droids were soon approached by the Jedi Master Qui-Gon Jinn, who was attempting to transport the Queen of Naboo, Padmé Amidala, off-world using the royal starship. After 2163 ordered Jinn and his companions be arrested, the Jedi cut down 1933 and the other droids with his lightsaber.

1933 first appeared in the 1999 prequel trilogy film, Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace. In the film, 1933's designation is not spoken, but the numbers are visible on the droid's comlink booster pack.
